==English==

===Pronunciation===
*bŭlk, /bʌlk/, /bVlk/

===Noun===
'''bulk''' ([[uncountable]])
# [[size]], [[mass]] or [[volume]]
# the [[major]] [[part]] of something
# (''in food'') [[fibre]]
# {{nautical}} a [[ship]]'s [[cargo]]
# {{bodybuilding}}: excess body [[mass]], especially [[muscle]]

====Translations====
French: masse

===Adjective===
'''bulk'''
# being [[large]] in size, mass or volume

====Translations====
*Portuguese: em massa

===Verb===
{{en-verb|bulk|bulks|bulked|bulking}}
# to be, or appear to be, [[massive]]
# to [[grow]] in size; to [[swell]] or [[expand]]

===Related terms===
*[[bulkhead]]
*[[bulky]]
*[[bulk up]]
*[[in bulk]]

